N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 191.4 - Sale of eggs to retailers or wholesalers

State Regulations
(a) For the purpose of this Part, a retailer
or wholesaler shall be deemed to be any person, firm or corporation buying eggs
for the purpose of resale. (b) Any
person selling eggs other than those of his own production shall furnish to the
retailer or wholesaler an invoice prior to or accompanying the delivery of
eggs. Notes
